# LAB 01 — VLAN Fundamentals (Cisco Packet Tracer)

## Overview
This lab demonstrates VLAN segmentation in a small office network using Cisco switches. It includes real-world baseline device configuration, VLAN creation, and port assignment.

## Objectives
- Configure basic switch security
- Create and name VLANs
- Assign switch ports to VLANs
- Disable unused ports for security
- Verify VLAN segmentation

## Topology
1 Switch (SW1)
3 PCs (HR, IT, Sales)

## VLANs
- VLAN 10: HR
- VLAN 20: IT
- VLAN 30: Sales

## Key Configurations
- Hostname setup
- Enable secret password
- Console and VTY access
- Service password encryption
- VLAN creation
- Port assignment
- Unused port shutdown

## Verification
- show vlan brief
- show running-config
- Ping tests between VLANs

## Result
Devices in different VLANs cannot communicate, confirming proper segmentation.

## Skills Learned
- VLAN configuration
- Switch hardening basics
- Port security fundamentals
- Network segmentation
